WEBVTT

00:00:55.661 --> 00:00:58.080
EPISODE 8

00:00:59.748 --> 00:01:02.501
You see, I grew up with nothing,

00:01:02.585 --> 00:01:04.461
like an orphaned child in wartime.

00:01:06.213 --> 00:01:07.840
You need a thick mask

00:01:07.923 --> 00:01:11.594
to pretend like nothing's wrong.

00:01:12.428 --> 00:01:13.470
Who exactly are you?

00:01:14.722 --> 00:01:16.599
Why did you approach me

00:01:16.682 --> 00:01:18.684
when you knew Su-ho?

00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:34.450
Do you think I blame you…

00:01:36.493 --> 00:01:38.078
for Su-ho's death?

00:01:42.833 --> 00:01:44.001
Or do you think…

00:01:46.003 --> 00:01:47.796
I'm getting revenge for him?

00:02:01.435 --> 00:02:03.687
Watching how a woman named Han Seol-ah

00:02:03.771 --> 00:02:06.523
made Su-ho swing between happiness,
sadness, and pain

00:02:06.607 --> 00:02:08.150
always made me wonder

00:02:08.776 --> 00:02:10.069
what kind of person she is.

00:02:11.403 --> 00:02:13.864
From the moment I met you,

00:02:15.449 --> 00:02:16.367
I knew

00:02:17.242 --> 00:02:19.370
you were a woman
a man would give his life for.

00:02:20.746 --> 00:02:21.789
Are you telling me…

00:02:23.916 --> 00:02:26.043
you fell for the woman

00:02:26.877 --> 00:02:28.504
who caused your friend's death?

00:02:31.924 --> 00:02:33.676
I wouldn't even dream about it

00:02:34.760 --> 00:02:36.637
if Su-ho were still alive.

00:02:36.720 --> 00:02:37.638
However,

00:02:38.138 --> 00:02:40.849
my friend is gone,

00:02:42.393 --> 00:02:45.229
and we're right here under the same sky.

00:02:50.859 --> 00:02:52.111
Is that it?

00:02:53.112 --> 00:02:55.030
What other truth do you need?

00:03:22.391 --> 00:03:24.893
-Mr. Paek, are you okay?
-What's going on?

00:03:25.477 --> 00:03:27.396
The fire alarm went off.
We're looking into it.

00:03:27.479 --> 00:03:28.522
Do it fast!

00:03:29.356 --> 00:03:30.649
Yes, sir.

00:03:34.611 --> 00:03:35.863
We can talk again another time.

00:03:44.371 --> 00:03:46.248
The fire alarm has been activated.

00:03:46.331 --> 00:03:49.334
Please evacuate all areas immediately.

00:03:49.418 --> 00:03:53.380
Do not use the elevators and proceed
to the nearest emergency stairs

00:03:53.464 --> 00:03:55.466
in a calm and orderly manner.

00:04:01.638 --> 00:04:02.514
Get in!

00:04:09.646 --> 00:04:10.481
YOUR HOME INTEGRATED CONTROL CENTER
CCTV SYSTEM

00:04:10.564 --> 00:04:11.523
Pause right there.

00:04:17.654 --> 00:04:18.781
Keep playing.

00:04:23.494 --> 00:04:24.495
Show me a different angle.

00:04:31.043 --> 00:04:31.919
Pause right there.

00:04:37.257 --> 00:04:38.258
A black cap.

00:05:00.114 --> 00:05:01.657
So it was Mr. Paek.

00:05:02.241 --> 00:05:03.534
He solicited murder.

00:05:04.284 --> 00:05:08.038
I didn't get to ask more questions
because the fire alarm went off.

00:05:08.122 --> 00:05:09.123
That was me.

00:05:10.415 --> 00:05:11.792
I was afraid you might be in danger.

00:05:38.652 --> 00:05:40.571
My office will make the arrangements.

00:05:40.654 --> 00:05:42.239
Stay out of the country for a while.

00:05:53.125 --> 00:05:55.627
I didn't expect this day to come so soon.

00:06:00.174 --> 00:06:03.302
If Mr. Paek tried to kill
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin,

00:06:04.469 --> 00:06:06.138
is it possible that he…

00:06:06.221 --> 00:06:07.681
He could've hurt someone else before.

00:06:09.266 --> 00:06:10.350
It doesn't make sense.

00:06:10.434 --> 00:06:12.853
Even if this is a revenge
on Su-ho's behalf,

00:06:12.936 --> 00:06:14.897
it's way too extreme.

00:06:17.024 --> 00:06:18.192
Paek Jun-beom

00:06:19.151 --> 00:06:21.945
probably knows by now
what was taken from the server,

00:06:22.529 --> 00:06:24.281
and he'll do whatever he thinks he has to.

00:06:25.407 --> 00:06:27.618
If we can track his movements after Syria
and put pressure on him--

00:06:27.701 --> 00:06:30.162
What if you become the next target?

00:06:31.914 --> 00:06:33.248
That works out even better.

00:06:34.082 --> 00:06:35.834
His henchman has been exposed,

00:06:35.918 --> 00:06:38.086
so he'll be forced to take action himself.

00:06:38.170 --> 00:06:39.630
Why are you being so reckless?

00:06:42.049 --> 00:06:43.008
Are you worried about me?

00:06:44.551 --> 00:06:45.427
Of course.

00:06:49.598 --> 00:06:50.641
Then that's all I need.

00:07:01.777 --> 00:07:04.029
AHN *****-SOO

00:07:07.574 --> 00:07:10.285
Mr. Ahn, how much longer
do I have to hide here?

00:07:10.369 --> 00:07:11.203
I'm sick of it.

00:07:12.704 --> 00:07:14.665
We're worried you'll be in danger again.

00:07:16.124 --> 00:07:18.210
My wife thinks I'm having an affair

00:07:18.293 --> 00:07:20.295
because I won't tell her where I am.

00:07:21.004 --> 00:07:23.382
Hey, that's a penalty for you.

00:07:24.633 --> 00:07:25.801
Why don't we play poker instead?

00:07:27.511 --> 00:07:28.679
-Mr. Cha!
-Hey.

00:07:31.223 --> 00:07:32.099
How are you feeling?

00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:35.560
The doctor said I should relieve stress,

00:07:35.644 --> 00:07:37.437
so I'm emptying Mr. Ahn's wallet
while I recover.

00:07:38.146 --> 00:07:40.107
He's a total card shark.

00:07:40.190 --> 00:07:41.483
My, look at that.

00:07:48.031 --> 00:07:51.493
But why would Jun-beom target me?

00:07:52.286 --> 00:07:53.662
I just can't believe it.

00:07:54.246 --> 00:07:56.206
He didn't want us to meet.

00:07:56.790 --> 00:07:58.000
There's definitely more

00:07:58.709 --> 00:08:01.128
to Lee Su-ho and Paek Jun-beom
than just their friendship.

00:08:01.211 --> 00:08:04.256
The Jun-beom I know
has no reason to do this,

00:08:04.339 --> 00:08:05.966
and he's not that kind of person either.

00:08:07.175 --> 00:08:09.636
Maybe he has a dark secret.

00:08:11.305 --> 00:08:12.973
Something that no one should ever know.

00:08:14.641 --> 00:08:16.184
Nothing comes to mind.

00:08:18.937 --> 00:08:21.231
Let me know if anything
that could be a clue comes to mind.

00:08:22.524 --> 00:08:24.026
The puzzle is almost complete,

00:08:25.277 --> 00:08:26.611
but we're missing

00:08:27.863 --> 00:08:29.114
the most important piece.

00:08:30.741 --> 00:08:32.534
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:08:32.617 --> 00:08:35.412
A travel ban has been issued
against Kim Sung-hae.

00:08:36.163 --> 00:08:39.750
There's enough evidence for hit-and-run
and attempted murder charges.

00:08:41.209 --> 00:08:42.753
Paek Jun-beom is the problem.

00:08:42.836 --> 00:08:44.921
The illegally obtained evidence
Woo-seok gave us isn't enough

00:08:45.005 --> 00:08:46.089
to prove murder for hire.

00:08:46.173 --> 00:08:49.384
Maybe he had Kim Sung-hae
kill Kim Yun-ji too.

00:08:49.468 --> 00:08:51.678
But what's Paek Jun-beom's motive?

00:08:51.762 --> 00:08:53.263
He's a man with a lot at stake.

00:08:54.222 --> 00:08:57.184
Isn't it usually a love affair
or a grudge in cases like this?

00:08:58.810 --> 00:09:00.562
Bring him in for questioning for now.

00:09:00.645 --> 00:09:02.064
Let's find out what kind of person he is.

00:09:02.814 --> 00:09:04.024
Yes, sir.

00:09:07.235 --> 00:09:08.487
Hello, Ms. Kwon.

00:09:08.570 --> 00:09:10.280
-Hello.
-What brings you here?

00:09:10.947 --> 00:09:12.657
I called, but you didn't answer.

00:09:13.283 --> 00:09:14.326
You called?

00:09:14.409 --> 00:09:15.243
Captain.

00:09:15.994 --> 00:09:18.288
Why don't you go home
with your wife tonight?

00:09:18.872 --> 00:09:20.207
No, that's okay.

00:09:20.290 --> 00:09:22.542
I thought I'd bring some late-night snacks
while dropping off his clean clothes.

00:09:23.335 --> 00:09:25.712
I'm guessing
you haven't had a proper meal yet.

00:09:28.632 --> 00:09:31.510
Wow, this isn't just any gimbap.

00:09:31.593 --> 00:09:32.469
It's chungmu gimbap, right?

00:09:32.552 --> 00:09:34.846
I figured you'd be tired
of regular gimbap.

00:09:34.930 --> 00:09:36.056
Thank you so much.

00:09:39.559 --> 00:09:42.646
CHA WOO-SEOK YEONGJONGDO ACCIDENT
ATTEMPTED MURDER OF LEE KWANG-JIN

00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:49.945
Let's sit down and eat.

00:09:50.028 --> 00:09:51.488
This looks so good.

00:10:04.459 --> 00:10:07.504
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:10:09.089 --> 00:10:11.466
The Taemyung Cultural Foundation accident?

00:10:14.136 --> 00:10:15.220
FINE ART
COMPREHENSIVE INSURANCE CLAIM FORM

00:10:15.303 --> 00:10:18.014
A truck crashed into a retaining wall
and caught fire,

00:10:18.098 --> 00:10:20.058
destroying five pieces.

00:10:20.142 --> 00:10:22.477
The insured amount alone
is ten billion won.

00:10:24.396 --> 00:10:25.939
DRIVING RECORD CERTIFICATE
NAME: HAN SEO-YUL

00:10:26.022 --> 00:10:27.691
The driver is 23 years old

00:10:28.400 --> 00:10:30.277
and had his license for less than a year.

00:10:31.653 --> 00:10:33.280
When transporting
high-value paintings like these,

00:10:33.363 --> 00:10:34.406
you never do it alone.

00:10:41.329 --> 00:10:42.998
There's a team of professional couriers.

00:10:43.081 --> 00:10:44.708
SPECIALIZING IN FINE ART & CULTURAL ASSETS

00:10:53.425 --> 00:10:56.344
And the most experienced driver
is always behind the wheel.

00:10:57.888 --> 00:11:00.182
Artworks worth ten billion won
would never be handled so poorly.

00:11:02.100 --> 00:11:04.811
We need to consider the possibility
of the accident being orchestrated.

00:11:04.895 --> 00:11:05.854
Anyway,

00:11:05.937 --> 00:11:07.814
refer this to the SIU
at general insurance.

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:10.442
This isn't our department.

00:11:11.193 --> 00:11:14.154
We actually need help from an art expert,

00:11:15.238 --> 00:11:18.825
and I hear
there's a bit of something going on…

00:11:20.702 --> 00:11:22.078
between you and Ms. Han at Royal Auction.

00:11:22.829 --> 00:11:23.830
Who said that?

00:11:33.048 --> 00:11:33.924
I'll ask her.

00:11:34.674 --> 00:11:35.592
Thank you, Mr. Cha.

00:11:40.514 --> 00:11:44.309
How many bidders have we secured so far
for the Stiller?

00:11:45.060 --> 00:11:47.229
We have 11,
including phone and absentee bidders.

00:11:48.396 --> 00:11:50.273
We only have three confirmed bidders,

00:11:50.357 --> 00:11:52.025
but we're still actively promoting it.

00:11:52.108 --> 00:11:54.319
It's a high-value piece,
so the bar is set high for bidders.

00:11:54.861 --> 00:11:57.822
I got calls from three people as well.

00:11:59.741 --> 00:12:03.203
The opening bids
will set the tone for this piece,

00:12:03.286 --> 00:12:05.872
so we need to create competition
from the start.

00:12:06.748 --> 00:12:09.960
Reach out to our regular VIP clients
and keep me updated.

00:12:10.544 --> 00:12:11.586
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

00:12:11.670 --> 00:12:13.296
And as for the catalog…

00:12:19.386 --> 00:12:22.013
Sang-mi, I'd like you to do
the final review.

00:12:22.973 --> 00:12:23.890
Yes, Ms. Han.

00:12:23.974 --> 00:12:25.809
That's it for today.

00:12:31.982 --> 00:12:33.775
You know,

00:12:33.858 --> 00:12:35.944
Yun-ji used to be in charge of that.

00:12:36.027 --> 00:12:37.445
Does this mean

00:12:37.529 --> 00:12:40.615
you'll be the associate auctioneer
for the upcoming auction?

00:12:41.283 --> 00:12:42.117
I'm not sure.

00:12:42.867 --> 00:12:44.452
Who knows what Ms. Han is thinking?

00:12:45.036 --> 00:12:46.454
Oh, man.

00:12:58.592 --> 00:13:00.093
FINE ART
COMPREHENSIVE INSURANCE CLAIM FORM

00:13:08.101 --> 00:13:09.185
The defendant, Ju Hyun-su,

00:13:09.269 --> 00:13:11.563
deliberately drove into a retaining wall
on an interchange on-ramp,

00:13:11.646 --> 00:13:14.441
causing the death of passenger,
Cha Woo-hee.

00:13:15.066 --> 00:13:17.193
The evidence from the crime scene
and insurance policy details

00:13:17.277 --> 00:13:20.280
demonstrates the defendant's intent
to kill the victim.

00:13:20.363 --> 00:13:22.657
Therefore, the prosecution requests
that the defendant be sentenced

00:13:22.741 --> 00:13:23.700
to ten years in prison.

00:13:37.297 --> 00:13:40.467
WOO-SEOK

00:13:41.092 --> 00:13:44.012
You read my mind.
I was just about to call you.

00:13:44.638 --> 00:13:45.805
Have you located Ju Hyun-su?

00:13:46.598 --> 00:13:50.060
Someone used his email
to create a delivery app account

00:13:50.143 --> 00:13:51.394
about a month ago.

00:13:52.854 --> 00:13:54.481
Find out his address.

00:13:54.564 --> 00:13:55.899
I'm on it.

00:14:39.484 --> 00:14:41.903
STAFF JU HYUN-SU

00:15:44.841 --> 00:15:47.385
I thought I told you to stay away
from Royal Auction.

00:15:48.386 --> 00:15:49.763
I technically work for the company too.

00:15:50.597 --> 00:15:53.641
I wanted to experience
tapping my card and clocking in.

00:15:55.226 --> 00:15:57.145
Didn't I tell you not to act rashly?

00:15:57.896 --> 00:16:00.565
I told you we needed to wrap up
the Taemyung deal without any issues.

00:16:03.902 --> 00:16:05.195
Don't worry.

00:16:05.779 --> 00:16:08.448
I poured my heart and soul into it
because it's my comeback project.

00:16:09.324 --> 00:16:12.076
I should at least get to experience
being served one of your famous meals.

00:16:14.078 --> 00:16:16.998
And once everything with Taemyung is over,
I expect my share.

00:16:18.416 --> 00:16:19.709
I won't be greedy.

00:16:19.793 --> 00:16:20.919
I think…

00:16:21.878 --> 00:16:22.754
10% ought to do it.

00:16:26.925 --> 00:16:28.718
You've got some nerve now, Ju Hyun-su.

00:16:29.844 --> 00:16:31.679
I only learned from the best.

00:17:07.549 --> 00:17:08.842
I saw this on the news.

00:17:08.925 --> 00:17:11.302
Is there a problem with the insurance?

00:17:11.386 --> 00:17:12.345
The truth is,

00:17:13.471 --> 00:17:15.515
it's similar to my sister's accident.

00:17:16.474 --> 00:17:17.433
What do you mean?

00:17:17.934 --> 00:17:19.602
Namcheonghyeon Interchange.

00:17:20.687 --> 00:17:22.564
The spot where the car
hit a retaining wall.

00:17:23.189 --> 00:17:24.566
Passenger-side impact only.

00:17:25.817 --> 00:17:27.485
Other than the fire,
everything else is the same.

00:17:28.236 --> 00:17:29.988
Criminals rely on familiar tactics

00:17:30.572 --> 00:17:32.490
and tend to repeat what's worked before.

00:17:33.408 --> 00:17:35.785
I'm looking into whether
the same person orchestrated this.

00:17:39.372 --> 00:17:40.874
I need your help.

00:17:53.219 --> 00:17:55.388
I handled the auction
for all these pieces.

00:17:55.471 --> 00:17:57.724
They came from overseas art galleries,

00:17:57.807 --> 00:17:59.893
but they turned out to be shell companies.

00:17:59.976 --> 00:18:03.062
The real owner was our chair.

00:18:04.856 --> 00:18:06.024
The chair of Royal Auction?

00:18:06.107 --> 00:18:08.693
She selects profitable pieces
for wealthy clients

00:18:08.776 --> 00:18:10.153
and takes a cut for herself
in the process.

00:18:11.738 --> 00:18:12.989
This piece here

00:18:13.740 --> 00:18:16.075
was secured by Taemyung Group
for 1.5 billion won,

00:18:16.784 --> 00:18:19.495
but it was brought in from overseas
for 300 million won.

00:18:21.497 --> 00:18:22.582
How is that possible?

00:18:22.665 --> 00:18:25.209
Paintings don't have a fixed value.

00:18:25.793 --> 00:18:28.129
If someone pays 1.5 billion won
for a painting,

00:18:28.212 --> 00:18:30.840
that becomes its value.

00:18:31.424 --> 00:18:32.300
Hold on.

00:18:33.801 --> 00:18:36.346
If you take out policies on the pieces
and burn them on purpose,

00:18:37.096 --> 00:18:39.098
it's possible to get back
that 1.5 billion won, right?

00:18:39.641 --> 00:18:42.727
People who deal with art
would never do that.

00:18:44.187 --> 00:18:46.940
They'd never burn an authentic piece.

00:18:47.607 --> 00:18:49.108
So they'd switch out the authentic pieces…

00:18:49.692 --> 00:18:51.069
And burn the forgeries.

00:18:54.405 --> 00:18:57.075
That's Chair Kim's tactic.

00:19:07.251 --> 00:19:08.920
There was a poor artist

00:19:09.420 --> 00:19:13.174
who was commissioned by Chair Kim
to paint replicas.

00:19:15.218 --> 00:19:18.429
Later, those replicas
were presented as authentic pieces,

00:19:18.513 --> 00:19:19.889
which sparked a huge scandal.

00:19:24.268 --> 00:19:25.770
No, my hand!

00:19:25.853 --> 00:19:27.730
No!

00:19:28.690 --> 00:19:29.607
No!

00:19:34.070 --> 00:19:36.990
You could at least be a little shameless.

00:19:37.824 --> 00:19:40.159
What were you thinking,
turning to loan sharks?

00:19:40.243 --> 00:19:42.370
Just look at you, Artist Han.

00:19:42.453 --> 00:19:43.705
Look at your hand.

00:19:47.458 --> 00:19:50.211
You can't hold a brush with that hand.

00:19:50.753 --> 00:19:53.840
The only thing that isn't damaged here
is that painting.

00:19:56.926 --> 00:19:59.345
If this becomes your posthumous piece,

00:20:00.263 --> 00:20:02.557
I'll make sure it sells for a high price.

00:20:02.640 --> 00:20:03.683
No!

00:20:03.766 --> 00:20:06.269
I'm begging you!
Please let me keep that one!

00:20:06.352 --> 00:20:08.354
The naive artist

00:20:08.938 --> 00:20:11.774
thought he was painting replicas
for an exhibition,

00:20:12.734 --> 00:20:14.027
but ended up

00:20:15.695 --> 00:20:17.196
taking the fall for everything.

00:20:19.949 --> 00:20:21.159
After that,

00:20:21.743 --> 00:20:24.954
he was hounded by loan sharks
and died with his family.

00:20:26.289 --> 00:20:27.582
Was that person…

00:20:31.127 --> 00:20:32.420
My father.

00:20:34.964 --> 00:20:36.549
I want to prove

00:20:37.133 --> 00:20:38.259
that my father

00:20:39.177 --> 00:20:40.678
wasn't that kind of person.

00:20:42.388 --> 00:20:43.765
So you joined Royal Auction because--

00:20:43.848 --> 00:20:45.767
I wanted to get revenge.

00:20:46.768 --> 00:20:47.769
But then…

00:20:49.395 --> 00:20:52.398
it became my only reason for living.

00:20:55.485 --> 00:20:56.486
I know how that feels.

00:20:58.029 --> 00:21:01.407
I'm also chasing the person
who ruined my life.

00:21:07.622 --> 00:21:08.915
We need to find out

00:21:09.582 --> 00:21:11.584
where the paintings
that were supposedly burned actually are.

00:21:12.835 --> 00:21:14.921
There's a secret storage vault
in the chair's suite.

00:21:31.437 --> 00:21:33.898
I've been trying to get in
for a long time,

00:21:33.981 --> 00:21:36.025
but I never got the opportunity.

00:21:36.609 --> 00:21:38.528
You need an expert investigator like me.

00:21:40.655 --> 00:21:44.158
And I need an informant
for this art insurance fraud case.

00:21:47.078 --> 00:21:48.287
Let's uncover…

00:21:50.706 --> 00:21:52.959
the hidden truth
inside that vault together.

00:22:18.234 --> 00:22:19.360
Damn it.

00:22:20.153 --> 00:22:21.946
This room is completely soundproof.

00:22:28.953 --> 00:22:29.954
What are you doing?

00:22:30.705 --> 00:22:32.957
Damn it, you scared me.

00:22:33.040 --> 00:22:34.333
There are people inside.

00:22:35.001 --> 00:22:35.918
Are there?

00:22:36.627 --> 00:22:39.130
It was quiet, so I thought it was empty.

00:22:41.090 --> 00:22:41.966
Later.

00:22:53.686 --> 00:22:55.438
MEET CHA WOO-SEOK,
THE GRIM REAPER OF INSURANCE FRAUD!

00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:02.320
SIU'S CHA WOO-SEOK WINS TOP HONOR
AT 2025 INSURANCE CRIME AWARDS

00:23:02.403 --> 00:23:05.656
He looks like an honest and reliable guy.

00:23:09.660 --> 00:23:11.746
Is there anything else I can do for you?

00:23:12.330 --> 00:23:14.540
I know I can be as good as Ms. Kim Yun-ji.

00:23:15.458 --> 00:23:17.752
Do you even know the full extent
of Ms. Kim's responsibilities?

00:23:18.461 --> 00:23:19.837
I know it to some extent.

00:23:21.005 --> 00:23:23.090
I may be inexperienced,
but I'll learn as I go.

00:23:23.925 --> 00:23:25.092
What I want

00:23:25.676 --> 00:23:28.095
isn't someone
who can be as good as Ms. Kim.

00:23:28.179 --> 00:23:29.931
I want someone at Ms. Han's level.

00:23:30.473 --> 00:23:33.226
You should, at the very least,
aim to be like Han Seol-ah.

00:23:34.352 --> 00:23:36.562
Keep reporting things to me for now.

00:23:37.730 --> 00:23:40.691
Yes, ma'am.
I'll provide detailed reports from now on.

00:23:49.033 --> 00:23:50.993
This is the painting
Mr. Paek consigned to me.

00:23:51.786 --> 00:23:53.829
There should be a clue in here somewhere.

00:23:55.957 --> 00:23:57.375
An Orphan from Syria.

00:23:57.458 --> 00:24:00.461
Su-ho grew up in an orphanage.

00:24:01.671 --> 00:24:03.172
We shared a similar background.

00:24:09.637 --> 00:24:10.972
Just how much

00:24:11.555 --> 00:24:13.724
has Mr. Paek heard about me?

00:24:15.935 --> 00:24:19.272
He knows me as well as Su-ho did.

00:24:22.608 --> 00:24:23.985
Let's find out who Paek Jun-beom is

00:24:25.236 --> 00:24:26.487
one step at a time.

00:24:34.161 --> 00:24:37.540
Could you tell me the exact reason
you were fired from Your Home?

00:24:37.623 --> 00:24:39.500
Before he went to Syria,

00:24:39.583 --> 00:24:43.129
I handled everything for Mr. Paek
and managed his daily schedule.

00:24:43.921 --> 00:24:46.757
But when he returned,
he suddenly told me to leave.

00:24:47.341 --> 00:24:48.509
I wasn't the only one.

00:24:48.592 --> 00:24:50.511
All the early employees got fired too.

00:24:52.513 --> 00:24:54.390
Do you remember anything else
from back then?

00:24:56.726 --> 00:24:59.353
The security system
in the offices and labs

00:24:59.854 --> 00:25:02.231
kept malfunctioning.

00:25:02.315 --> 00:25:04.567
It was customized for Mr. Paek,

00:25:04.650 --> 00:25:06.193
but the errors kept happening,

00:25:06.277 --> 00:25:08.696
so he eventually had
the whole system replaced.

00:25:09.613 --> 00:25:10.906
Errors?

00:25:10.990 --> 00:25:13.534
The system used iris recognition,

00:25:14.201 --> 00:25:17.705
but strangely,
it couldn't recognize Mr. Paek himself.

00:25:18.956 --> 00:25:22.501
So he called a security company
to replace the entire system.

00:25:23.794 --> 00:25:24.920
It failed to recognize him,

00:25:25.921 --> 00:25:27.298
even though it was him?

00:25:27.798 --> 00:25:28.632
Yes.

00:25:32.845 --> 00:25:34.263
His irises are different?

00:25:34.347 --> 00:25:37.308
No amount of surgery
can change your iris patterns.

00:25:37.892 --> 00:25:41.020
It could be someone
impersonating Paek Jun-beom.

00:25:41.937 --> 00:25:43.773
Here's what you asked for.

00:25:44.398 --> 00:25:45.691
Thank you.

00:25:46.525 --> 00:25:49.236
Why did you ask me to gather
photos of only this person?

00:25:49.820 --> 00:25:50.988
I'll tell you later.

00:25:51.072 --> 00:25:52.698
Where are you going?

00:25:53.783 --> 00:25:56.660
Are you looking into Paek Jun-beom?

00:26:02.792 --> 00:26:03.834
Paek Jun-beom

00:26:04.668 --> 00:26:06.045
was friends with Lee Su-ho?

00:26:06.629 --> 00:26:08.714
He approached me intentionally.

00:26:09.382 --> 00:26:12.426
I need to find out
what his real intentions are.

00:26:12.510 --> 00:26:14.387
Are you saying
everything that happened to you

00:26:14.470 --> 00:26:15.888
wasn't just a coincidence?

00:26:16.472 --> 00:26:17.306
Yeah.

00:26:18.099 --> 00:26:19.266
That's what I think.

00:26:20.267 --> 00:26:21.811
Why didn't you tell me sooner

00:26:21.894 --> 00:26:23.854
instead of going to that SIU investigator?

00:26:24.438 --> 00:26:25.815
I can help you too, you know.

00:26:26.482 --> 00:26:30.653
He and I are sharing information
because it helps both of us.

00:26:31.237 --> 00:26:33.322
I'm a bit hurt.

00:26:33.906 --> 00:26:37.118
It feels like you're relying
on that investigator more than me.

00:26:38.577 --> 00:26:39.870
It's not so much relying on him,

00:26:41.414 --> 00:26:43.624
but he's similar to us in a way.

00:26:45.084 --> 00:26:46.877
And we recognized that in each other.

00:26:48.087 --> 00:26:49.463
The way you and I did.

00:26:55.970 --> 00:26:57.763
I know Paek Jun-beom very well.

00:26:58.722 --> 00:27:02.226
I heard you two were
in the same start-up club back in college.

00:27:03.060 --> 00:27:05.855
He used to be so thoughtful
toward everyone around him,

00:27:05.938 --> 00:27:08.357
but I heard he's completely changed
once his start-up took off.

00:27:09.483 --> 00:27:12.153
Have you lost all contact with him, then?

00:27:12.236 --> 00:27:14.447
I heard he had injured his face,

00:27:14.530 --> 00:27:16.699
so I thought that was why
he avoided people.

00:27:16.782 --> 00:27:19.076
But I saw him at a conference,
and he looked fine.

00:27:19.577 --> 00:27:21.287
I think he's even better-looking now.

00:27:21.871 --> 00:27:24.665
But when I greeted him,
he ignored me like I was a stranger.

00:27:25.583 --> 00:27:28.085
I heard he's lost touch
with the rest of his friends.

00:27:28.169 --> 00:27:29.462
Do you know why?

00:27:30.629 --> 00:27:32.089
I'd like to know myself.

00:27:32.173 --> 00:27:34.175
It's hard to believe
how someone can change that drastically.

00:27:38.179 --> 00:27:39.972
That bastard

00:27:40.055 --> 00:27:42.892
injected the anesthetic like this

00:27:42.975 --> 00:27:44.435
while I was squinting, watching him.

00:27:44.518 --> 00:27:47.438
Cold sweat just ran down my back.

00:27:47.521 --> 00:27:48.731
And then what?

00:27:48.814 --> 00:27:50.191
I pretended to be asleep.

00:27:50.274 --> 00:27:51.233
Man.

00:27:51.317 --> 00:27:52.776
If that IV had really been in you,

00:27:52.860 --> 00:27:55.112
you could've died instead of me.

00:27:55.196 --> 00:27:57.448
I risked my life for this mission.

00:27:57.531 --> 00:28:01.785
I was even ready to take him on
if he had found out I was a fake.

00:28:03.454 --> 00:28:04.997
Are you also a former detective?

00:28:06.040 --> 00:28:07.208
No.

00:28:07.291 --> 00:28:09.793
I'm better at using my head,
so I took an exam to get this job.

00:28:10.878 --> 00:28:11.837
In any case,

00:28:12.463 --> 00:28:13.797
I'm glad you didn't get caught.

00:28:13.881 --> 00:28:17.843
I mean, we do look similar
when our faces are covered, don't we?

00:28:18.969 --> 00:28:19.845
No, not at all.

00:28:23.599 --> 00:28:25.142
Call Mr. Cha.

00:28:26.435 --> 00:28:27.353
DNA.

00:28:29.647 --> 00:28:31.398
Since we often go to conflict zones,

00:28:31.482 --> 00:28:33.150
we store DNA samples for identification

00:28:33.234 --> 00:28:35.611
in case something goes wrong.

00:28:35.694 --> 00:28:38.531
OnWorld has Su-ho
and Jun-beom's DNA information.

00:28:41.116 --> 00:28:42.201
Now we can finally find out

00:28:43.160 --> 00:28:44.995
what Paek Jun-Beom was trying to hide.

00:30:10.372 --> 00:30:11.290
An invitation?

00:30:11.373 --> 00:30:15.502
It's for a preview event
for our VVIP clients,

00:30:15.586 --> 00:30:19.131
and it'll also be the first public showing
of the Stiller.

00:30:19.214 --> 00:30:20.257
Then I should attend.

00:30:20.758 --> 00:30:22.134
That piece meant a great deal to me.

00:30:56.752 --> 00:31:01.048
In 2013, Stiller sought to visualize
"layers of memory."

00:31:01.799 --> 00:31:04.259
The thick, overlapping blues

00:31:04.343 --> 00:31:06.762
and repeating geometric patterns

00:31:06.845 --> 00:31:11.392
served as a metaphor
for the passage and erosion of time.

00:31:11.975 --> 00:31:14.853
These red lines,
which appear to form a frame,

00:31:15.437 --> 00:31:18.107
were used to amplify disorder.

00:31:18.190 --> 00:31:21.235
Through this approach,
Stiller captured what he described

00:31:21.318 --> 00:31:24.113
as "the moment memory engulfs
its own borders."

00:31:29.660 --> 00:31:31.745
He's much better looking
than the rumors claim.

00:31:31.829 --> 00:31:33.288
I hear he's still single.

00:31:44.633 --> 00:31:46.635
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin
wanted me to send his regards.

00:31:49.138 --> 00:31:50.097
He says he's well…

00:31:51.807 --> 00:31:52.891
and wants to see you.

00:31:56.812 --> 00:31:57.730
I'm glad to hear that.

00:31:58.439 --> 00:32:01.984
Mr. Lee is also the only person
I want to see.

00:32:04.445 --> 00:32:05.696
Is that so?

00:32:09.783 --> 00:32:11.952
Do you usually act differently
from how you really feel?

00:32:14.079 --> 00:32:16.290
It's not too late
to make the right decision.

00:32:17.750 --> 00:32:20.919
It's best to turn yourself in
rather than get arrested.

00:32:21.503 --> 00:32:22.671
It looks better that way,

00:32:24.214 --> 00:32:25.299
and it could reduce your sentence.

00:32:28.177 --> 00:32:29.720
It sounds like it'd be fun,

00:32:29.803 --> 00:32:31.972
but I don't know
if I'll ever step foot in a police station

00:32:33.515 --> 00:32:36.143
because I have a very capable legal team.

00:32:39.271 --> 00:32:42.232
You must be very upset about the accident.

00:32:42.316 --> 00:32:45.027
The value of those paintings
increased greatly after I won them.

00:32:45.110 --> 00:32:47.738
It's a huge loss since it was
more than just a few paintings.

00:32:47.821 --> 00:32:51.241
We take out insurance policies
for exactly these kinds of situations.

00:32:52.242 --> 00:32:55.996
Ms. Han, I hear you know
the insurance account manager well.

00:32:56.830 --> 00:32:57.664
Is that so?

00:32:57.748 --> 00:32:59.750
Take extra care
that this is processed smoothly.

00:33:01.168 --> 00:33:02.461
Yes, Chair Kim.

00:33:03.253 --> 00:33:04.755
Don't worry about a thing.

00:33:04.838 --> 00:33:06.757
You know how good Ms. Han is at her job.

00:33:08.175 --> 00:33:12.012
You can buy even better paintings
once you receive the compensation.

00:33:12.513 --> 00:33:14.181
I'll recommend some again.

00:33:16.141 --> 00:33:17.059
This right here

00:33:17.142 --> 00:33:20.479
is the Stiller
that will be at the next auction.

00:33:21.647 --> 00:33:25.692
There aren't many Stillers left,
so they're extremely valuable,

00:33:25.776 --> 00:33:27.778
and since this will be the first one
auctioned in Korea,

00:33:27.861 --> 00:33:29.822
the competition will be fierce.

00:33:36.495 --> 00:33:37.746
Excuse me, Mr. Paek.

00:33:37.830 --> 00:33:40.833
Chair Kim would like to see you privately.
Would that be okay?

00:33:42.251 --> 00:33:43.585
Sure.

00:33:46.129 --> 00:33:49.299
I guess parties really aren't my thing.

00:33:51.802 --> 00:33:53.679
I feel very uncomfortable.

00:33:56.849 --> 00:33:57.850
At times like that,

00:33:58.433 --> 00:34:00.227
you should try to relax.

00:34:16.577 --> 00:34:18.579
Right, you're still on the job.

00:34:19.496 --> 00:34:20.414
Yes.

00:34:33.760 --> 00:34:34.970
Are you okay?

00:34:38.098 --> 00:34:38.932
Mr. Paek!

00:34:41.018 --> 00:34:43.061
Mr. Paek Jun-beom, can you hear me?

00:34:53.947 --> 00:34:55.157
What's wrong with him?

00:34:57.367 --> 00:34:59.161
He's in anaphylactic shock.

00:34:59.244 --> 00:35:01.121
With symptoms this severe,
he should have an injector on him.

00:35:24.353 --> 00:35:26.897
-Is he dead?
-Oh, my gosh.

00:35:29.858 --> 00:35:30.984
I think he's getting better.

00:36:01.014 --> 00:36:02.057
Where are you? Get here now.

00:36:09.648 --> 00:36:10.565
Where's the sample?

00:36:12.192 --> 00:36:13.860
-Here.
-What the heck?

00:36:20.033 --> 00:36:22.035
What on earth did you do?

00:36:22.119 --> 00:36:23.578
We'll get accurate results for sure.

00:36:24.246 --> 00:36:25.414
-Step on it.
-Yes, sir.

00:36:44.641 --> 00:36:46.309
He's in anaphylactic shock.

00:36:46.393 --> 00:36:48.270
With symptoms this severe,
he should have an injector on him.

00:36:53.775 --> 00:36:55.694
Watching how a woman named Han Seol-ah

00:36:56.403 --> 00:37:00.240
made Su-ho swing between happiness,
sadness, and pain

00:37:00.323 --> 00:37:01.825
always made me wonder

00:37:03.160 --> 00:37:04.327
what kind of person she is.

00:37:05.579 --> 00:37:08.540
I wouldn't even dream about it
if Su-ho were still alive.

00:37:09.207 --> 00:37:10.083
However,

00:37:11.043 --> 00:37:12.836
my friend is gone,

00:37:14.296 --> 00:37:15.714
and we're right here

00:37:16.757 --> 00:37:18.008
under the same sky.

00:37:35.067 --> 00:37:37.360
What a commotion at a VIP event.

00:37:38.570 --> 00:37:40.155
Mr. Song, just a moment!

00:37:41.323 --> 00:37:42.324
Hey, hurry up.

00:37:43.825 --> 00:37:44.785
You were serving drinks, right?

00:37:44.868 --> 00:37:45.952
What happened?

00:37:47.204 --> 00:37:49.956
Mr. Paek collapsed
after drinking champagne.

00:37:51.041 --> 00:37:52.042
But more importantly, here.

00:37:53.210 --> 00:37:54.169
What is it?

00:37:57.464 --> 00:37:59.299
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

00:37:59.382 --> 00:38:01.510
5. HYUN-SU'S FRUIT, 6. COUNTRY HOUSE,
7. BITNA TOWN BUILDING, 8. ROYAL VILLAT…

00:38:04.304 --> 00:38:07.182
WORKS IN FELIX STORAGE

00:38:08.642 --> 00:38:09.726
What's this?

00:38:09.810 --> 00:38:13.355
I stole it from Han Seol-ah's desk
during the commotion earlier.

00:38:14.815 --> 00:38:16.733
You've got absolutely no fear, do you?

00:38:17.317 --> 00:38:19.027
You told me not to coast by.

00:38:19.611 --> 00:38:20.487
Right.

00:38:24.116 --> 00:38:25.617
Would you look at that.

00:38:26.368 --> 00:38:29.329
They say you should never trust people.

00:38:30.497 --> 00:38:33.291
She's been digging up dirt on Chair Kim
behind her back, huh?

00:39:07.826 --> 00:39:09.661
It's 110 over 70.

00:39:14.332 --> 00:39:16.585
Your numbers are back to normal,

00:39:16.668 --> 00:39:18.336
but should I have Dr. Jeong on standby?

00:39:19.379 --> 00:39:20.255
No, I'm fine.

00:39:38.732 --> 00:39:39.608
Take a seat.

00:39:48.658 --> 00:39:50.285
Is the event over?

00:39:52.537 --> 00:39:53.663
Not yet.

00:39:55.415 --> 00:39:56.416
Then what brings you here?

00:39:58.084 --> 00:40:00.337
I was afraid I wouldn't have
another opportunity if not today.

00:40:05.967 --> 00:40:08.011
Isn't there something

00:40:09.387 --> 00:40:10.722
you really want to say to me?

00:40:15.143 --> 00:40:16.978
It's finally come to this.

00:40:21.149 --> 00:40:22.567
There's somewhere we need to go.

00:40:24.945 --> 00:40:26.279
I want to show you something.

00:42:02.709 --> 00:42:04.502
Someday, way down the road,

00:42:05.170 --> 00:42:06.796
I want us to build our home

00:42:06.880 --> 00:42:08.340
in the woods.

00:42:08.923 --> 00:42:10.884
-What?
-A two-story house.

00:42:16.639 --> 00:42:18.183
I want a big front yard

00:42:19.392 --> 00:42:21.478
so our kids can run around
and play all day.

00:42:22.312 --> 00:42:24.189
I'm going to line the path to our house

00:42:25.482 --> 00:42:27.692
with your favorite birch trees.

00:42:28.360 --> 00:42:30.445
We'll have a small swing on the lawn

00:42:31.237 --> 00:42:34.032
for us to sit on with our kids
whenever we like.

00:42:43.541 --> 00:42:44.751
Seol-ah, where are you?

00:42:48.588 --> 00:42:49.547
POWERING OFF

00:43:02.685 --> 00:43:04.479
I picked and cleared the land
in the first year

00:43:04.979 --> 00:43:06.648
and built the house the following year.

00:43:08.650 --> 00:43:09.984
I had a hand in everything,

00:43:11.778 --> 00:43:13.405
from the stone slabs to the roof

00:43:14.989 --> 00:43:16.616
and every tree.

00:43:21.663 --> 00:43:24.082
I wanted you
to be the first to see this place.

00:43:27.377 --> 00:43:28.420
Aren't you cold?

00:43:28.503 --> 00:43:29.337
Just a moment.

00:43:32.298 --> 00:43:33.133
Oh, right.

00:43:33.883 --> 00:43:35.427
You don't like fires.

00:43:39.347 --> 00:43:40.390
Su-ho.

00:43:56.197 --> 00:43:57.866
I compared the blood from the injector

00:43:57.949 --> 00:44:00.743
with the samples
from Lee Su-ho and Paek Jun-beom,

00:44:00.827 --> 00:44:01.911
and it matches

00:44:02.662 --> 00:44:05.665
Lee Su-ho's STR profile.

00:44:11.921 --> 00:44:13.423
SAMPLE 1 - SAMPLE 2 RESULT

00:44:16.092 --> 00:44:17.927
SAMPLE 1: LEE SU-HO
SAMPLE 2: PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:44:20.138 --> 00:44:22.390
ANALYSIS INDICATES A COMPLETE MATCH

00:44:22.474 --> 00:44:24.100
SAMPLE 1 AND SAMPLE 2
ARE FROM THE SAME INDIVIDUAL

00:44:24.184 --> 00:44:25.143
So, he's not Paek Jun-beom.

00:44:25.768 --> 00:44:26.769
He's Lee Su-ho.

00:44:27.812 --> 00:44:29.606
Paek Jun-beom died in Syria.

00:44:36.404 --> 00:44:39.532
The phone you are trying to reach
is turned off. You will be directed to--

00:44:42.243 --> 00:44:43.244
Mr. Cha!

00:45:43.596 --> 00:45:45.557
It didn't feel like my name anymore…

00:45:49.644 --> 00:45:51.312
but hearing you say it
makes it feel different.

00:45:52.772 --> 00:45:54.232
It feels like I'm back in the past.

00:45:59.070 --> 00:46:00.405
I was actually worried…

00:46:03.408 --> 00:46:05.076
that you'd recognize me immediately.

00:46:06.786 --> 00:46:07.662
But you…

00:46:09.330 --> 00:46:10.748
You only had eyes for the painting…

00:46:12.667 --> 00:46:14.335
that Paek Jun-beom, the VIP, owned.

00:46:16.879 --> 00:46:17.880
What's wrong?

00:46:18.881 --> 00:46:20.550
You were testing whether it was really me,
weren't you?

00:46:23.177 --> 00:46:25.305
You put something in the champagne,
didn't you?

00:46:28.057 --> 00:46:29.309
How can you be…

00:46:29.934 --> 00:46:31.060
How can I be Lee Su-ho?

00:46:33.938 --> 00:46:34.856
Seol-ah.

00:46:38.192 --> 00:46:39.319
Go to TH Hotel.

00:46:39.402 --> 00:46:40.445
Take good care of him.

00:46:41.070 --> 00:46:43.156
What's the matter with you?
I'm late for a meeting.

00:46:43.239 --> 00:46:46.200
I'm leaving for Syria tomorrow.

00:46:46.784 --> 00:46:47.952
I already told you.

00:46:48.578 --> 00:46:50.413
Work is more important to me.

00:46:51.205 --> 00:46:52.999
Does the world look different
now that you're at Royal Auction?

00:46:53.082 --> 00:46:55.918
You think there's no future with me
since I have nothing?

00:46:56.919 --> 00:46:57.795
Yeah.

00:47:05.386 --> 00:47:07.597
SEOL-AH

00:47:40.213 --> 00:47:41.047
You're the one…

00:47:44.300 --> 00:47:45.635
who killed me.

00:47:47.804 --> 00:47:48.846
That's not me anymore.

00:47:49.597 --> 00:47:54.060
The idiot who chose to end his life
just to be remembered by you…

00:47:57.605 --> 00:47:58.773
is dead.

00:48:03.152 --> 00:48:04.987
Life is ironic, isn't it?

00:48:05.571 --> 00:48:06.948
It's funny how my clothes

00:48:07.031 --> 00:48:09.492
got switched with Jun-beom's that day.

00:48:09.575 --> 00:48:10.827
We have a patient!

00:48:10.910 --> 00:48:12.328
Jun-beom, stay with me!

00:48:12.912 --> 00:48:14.622
You're going to be okay.
Just hang in there.

00:48:14.706 --> 00:48:16.124
You'll be okay.

00:48:17.792 --> 00:48:18.668
Make room!

00:48:20.253 --> 00:48:22.213
My friend who tried to save me died,

00:48:23.005 --> 00:48:25.049
and I survived instead.

00:48:25.133 --> 00:48:26.676
SURGERY STATUS
PAEK JUN-****: IN SURGERY

00:48:27.719 --> 00:48:30.304
The medical staff
thought I was Paek Jun-beom.

00:48:34.392 --> 00:48:36.561
I had to undergo reconstructive surgery

00:48:36.644 --> 00:48:38.146
on my completely damaged face
and vocal cords.

00:48:48.948 --> 00:48:50.408
After dozens of operations…

00:48:52.452 --> 00:48:54.162
my face turned into my friend's.

00:48:57.623 --> 00:48:59.125
I started a new life…

00:49:02.378 --> 00:49:03.921
with a different face,

00:49:05.298 --> 00:49:07.300
a different name,
and even a different voice.

00:49:09.927 --> 00:49:11.137
I became Paek Jun-beom.

00:49:13.389 --> 00:49:14.766
When I came back,

00:49:15.391 --> 00:49:17.560
I realized how stupid I was.

00:49:18.644 --> 00:49:21.439
You didn't even care if I had died or not.

00:49:24.150 --> 00:49:25.610
Did you like money that much?

00:49:25.693 --> 00:49:28.237
So much that you'd follow an old man
into a hotel room?

00:49:28.905 --> 00:49:30.239
That was for work.

00:49:30.740 --> 00:49:32.074
It's not what you think at all.

00:49:34.577 --> 00:49:36.412
So what are you doing right now?

00:49:36.496 --> 00:49:39.582
The Lee Su-ho you dumped
was pathetic in every way,

00:49:40.500 --> 00:49:42.418
but Paek Jun-beom's life was different.

00:49:56.182 --> 00:49:58.226
This is our private viewing room.

00:49:58.935 --> 00:50:00.144
Please head inside.

00:50:06.317 --> 00:50:08.528
Yes, Paddle 86. We have 5.3 billion.

00:50:10.238 --> 00:50:11.072
Congratulations.

00:50:16.619 --> 00:50:19.664
I didn't realize success
could feel so sweet, comfortable,

00:50:20.498 --> 00:50:21.916
and empowering.

00:50:22.875 --> 00:50:24.794
I didn't know life could be like this.

00:50:24.877 --> 00:50:25.837
And then

00:50:26.921 --> 00:50:28.214
I got curious.

00:50:32.343 --> 00:50:35.888
I wondered if I could seduce you
with my wealth.

00:50:38.099 --> 00:50:39.267
But at the same time,

00:50:39.851 --> 00:50:41.686
I hoped you wouldn't fall for it.

00:50:48.776 --> 00:50:49.610
You…

00:50:50.570 --> 00:50:51.904
You really are Lee Su-ho.

00:50:53.948 --> 00:50:55.449
Lee Su-ho, the idiot.

00:50:57.702 --> 00:51:00.454
When you have nothing,
the only thing you can bet on is yourself.

00:51:01.747 --> 00:51:03.875
I hated you as much as I had loved you.

00:51:04.876 --> 00:51:06.961
I wanted to get revenge,
even if it meant dying.

00:51:10.047 --> 00:51:11.382
I'm at Paek Jun-beom's house.

00:51:12.258 --> 00:51:13.301
Damn it.

00:51:14.760 --> 00:51:16.929
I can't reach either of them.
Track their location.

00:51:17.013 --> 00:51:18.598
You need to move out right now!

00:51:19.640 --> 00:51:20.600
You know the captain.

00:51:21.183 --> 00:51:22.977
He won't mobilize people
over something like that.

00:51:23.936 --> 00:51:25.354
What's going on?

00:51:25.438 --> 00:51:26.939
I don't have time to explain.

00:51:29.025 --> 00:51:31.193
Then tell him to come
and catch me in the act.

00:51:31.277 --> 00:51:32.653
What are you going to do?

00:51:33.321 --> 00:51:34.906
I'm going to kill Paek Jun-beom.

00:51:36.157 --> 00:51:37.158
Hey, Cha Woo-seok!

00:51:38.451 --> 00:51:39.410
Damn it.

00:52:08.314 --> 00:52:09.231
Damn it!

00:52:32.213 --> 00:52:33.547
APPROACHED SEOL-AH
AFTER THE KIM YUN-JI CASE

00:52:34.840 --> 00:52:37.009
DO EUN-HYUK, JUST A FRIEND?
HWANG SUK-JI, OVERLY OBSESSED WITH SEOL-AH

00:52:37.093 --> 00:52:38.886
KIM YUN-JI (ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER)

00:52:38.970 --> 00:52:39.845
CHA WOO-SEOK (SIU INVESTIGATOR)

00:52:41.597 --> 00:52:44.183
DATED, THEN PROPOSED
YOON SEUNG-JAE, OWNER OF THE GALLERY

00:52:53.693 --> 00:52:56.570
HAN SEOL-AH

00:52:57.655 --> 00:52:58.739
SEOL-AH AFTER WORK

00:52:58.823 --> 00:53:00.908
SEOL-AH RUNNING AN AUCTION

00:53:04.787 --> 00:53:06.998
If I had come back as Lee Su-ho,

00:53:08.082 --> 00:53:09.375
would you have even looked my way?

00:53:10.501 --> 00:53:13.587
You only smiled at me after I won a bid
worth billions of won.

00:53:13.671 --> 00:53:17.508
You came running to charm me
when you found out I owned a Stiller!

00:53:19.051 --> 00:53:20.553
And like a moron…

00:53:22.638 --> 00:53:24.515
I was swayed.

00:53:27.268 --> 00:53:29.478
I wanted to make you my woman again!

00:53:31.355 --> 00:53:33.107
We can be happy together, Seol-ah.

00:53:33.190 --> 00:53:35.151
I'm Paek Jun-beom. I can do anything.

00:53:35.234 --> 00:53:37.278
I'll give you everything you want.

00:53:37.361 --> 00:53:38.362
You've lost your mind!

00:53:41.615 --> 00:53:43.284
Why can't we be together?

00:53:45.453 --> 00:53:46.287
Wait.

00:53:49.290 --> 00:53:51.709
Don't tell me
it's because of Cha Woo-seok.

00:53:57.882 --> 00:53:59.008
Do you like that bastard?

00:54:03.012 --> 00:54:05.973
DATED, THEN PROPOSED
YOON SEUNG-JAE, OWNER OF THE GALLERY

00:54:12.271 --> 00:54:13.355
CHA WOO-SEOK (SIU INVESTIGATOR)

00:54:14.231 --> 00:54:15.941
DO EUN-HYUK, JUST A FRIEND?
HWANG SUK-JI, OVERLY OBSESSED WITH SEOL-AH

00:54:21.238 --> 00:54:22.615
Make up your mind.

00:54:35.753 --> 00:54:37.296
Locate Paek Jun-beom right now

00:54:37.379 --> 00:54:38.714
and mobilize everyone.

00:54:40.925 --> 00:54:42.093
Let him go.

00:54:59.068 --> 00:55:00.486
The last location
before the signal dropped

00:55:00.569 --> 00:55:02.780
was 866, Jicheon-myeon, Yangpyeong-gun.

00:55:09.120 --> 00:55:10.037
Stop it!

00:55:10.121 --> 00:55:11.122
Get away from me!

00:55:16.418 --> 00:55:17.253
Don't come near me.

00:55:20.214 --> 00:55:21.382
Don't come near me.

00:55:22.466 --> 00:55:24.385
I've already died once because of you.

00:55:25.344 --> 00:55:27.346
I can do it again.

00:55:28.889 --> 00:55:33.185
I have no intention of ever leaving you
in this lifetime, Seol-ah.

00:56:02.047 --> 00:56:03.048
HAN SEOL-AH

00:56:03.132 --> 00:56:06.051
The phone you are trying to reach
is turned off.

00:56:06.135 --> 00:56:08.262
You will be directed to voicemail
after the beep and charges will apply.

00:58:06.547 --> 00:58:07.381
Don't move.

00:59:44.812 --> 00:59:45.813
Let go of me!

00:59:45.896 --> 00:59:47.147
It's a murder case!

00:59:47.815 --> 00:59:49.316
Just let me see her once.

00:59:49.400 --> 00:59:51.527
They all felt pity for me

00:59:52.486 --> 00:59:54.321
and said they'd do anything for me,

00:59:54.405 --> 00:59:56.490
so I told them to do what my parents did

00:59:57.074 --> 00:59:58.534
and take out an insurance policy and die.

00:59:59.785 --> 01:00:01.412
If there was someone else…

01:00:02.079 --> 01:00:03.330
Don't relax just yet.

01:00:03.414 --> 01:00:05.582
She's still the prime suspect.

01:00:06.125 --> 01:00:07.709
Cha Woo-seok really cares.

01:00:08.335 --> 01:00:09.670
Thank you for everything.

01:00:11.171 --> 01:00:12.673
Thank you for helping me

01:00:13.298 --> 01:00:14.508
and believing me.

01:00:15.717 --> 01:00:17.719
Subtitle: Jenny Kim